      "content": "I've dug deeper into the logs, and it appears that the database connection issue is related to the API gateway's endpoint connectivity. Specifically, I found a few entries indicating that the endpoint lifecycle is not properly handling certain types of requests. These errors are related to the recent migration of endpoint configurations.\n\nIt seems that the migration process didn't update the endpoint lifecycle manager correctly, leading to a few issues:\n\n1. A \"Endpoint Not Found\" error for requests to the newly migrated endpoints.\n2. An \"Invalid Request\" error for requests that are trying to use deprecated endpoint configurations.\n\nThe error logs indicate that these issues are being flagged by the API gateway's endpoint connectivity module, which is attempting to resolve the errors through automatic retries.\n\nHowever, I did find a few entries suggesting that the endpoint connectivity module is also experiencing some issues with the new endpoint configurations. These errors are related to the \"endpoint discovery\" process, which is responsible for detecting and registering new endpoints with the API gateway.\n\nThe errors are not directly related to the deprecation notices, but rather a separate issue that may be causing the API gateway to misinterpret the endpoint configurations. I recommend investigating this further to ensure that the endpoint lifecycle manager is properly updated and configured for the holiday rush.",
